# IntelliJ - attempting to be consistent with
#   https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544839-How-to-manage-projects-under-Version-Control-Systems
# but then IntelliJ seems to generate .idea/.gitignore too, which knocks out some of the stuff that
# mentions
*/.idea/usage.statistics.xml
# libraries isn't in above doc, but simply doesn't seem like what we want ...
.idea/libraries/

# exclude .iml, modules.xml due bc including them doesn't cause repo to behave well w Intellij
# and seems we don't *need* to commit them
# https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544839-How-to-manage-projects-under-Version-Control-Systems
.idea/modules.xml
*.iml

# IntelliJ config file created IFF you have terraform plugin installed; this includes paths on your machine couple to how terraform is installed,
# so I dont' think a good idea to commit it
.idea/terraform.xml

# bunch of github copilot files???
.idea/copilot.*

# macOs generated files
.DS_Store

# Log files
*.log

# local maven cache
.m2/
.azure/

